<DL><DT><H2><A NAME="1.">1. E-mail</A></H2>
<DT>Documents arrive faster than overnight
<DT>Documents sent by e-mail are better than facsimiles because they print more clearly and can
be edited
<DT>Encryption programs:
<DD>Crypt-o-Text
<DL><DD><a
href="http://www.owt.com/users/rsavard/files/ct16-122.zip">http://www.owt.com/users/rsavard/files/ct16-122.zip</a>(16 bit)
<DD><a
href="http://www.owt.com/users/rsavard/files/ct32-122.zip">http://www.owt.com/users/rsavard/files/ct32-122.zip</a>(32 bit)</DL>
<DD>PGP
<DL><DD><a
href="http://bs.mit.edu:8001/pgp-form.html">http://bs.mit.edu:8001/pgp-form.html</a></DL>
<DD>PKZIP/WinZip
<DL><DD><a
href="ftp://ftp2.winzip.com/winzip/winzip31.exe">ftp://ftp2.winzip.com/winzip/winzip31.exe</a>(16 bit)
<DD><a
href="ftp://ftp2.winzip.com/winzip/winzip95.exe">ftp://ftp2.winzip.com/winzip/winzip95.exe</a>(32 bit)</DL>
<DT>E-mail-to-fax services
<DD><a
href="ftp://rtfm.mit.edu/pub/usenet/news.answers/internet-services/fax-faq">ftp://rtfm.mit.edu/pub/usenet/news.answers/internet-services/fax-faq</a>
<DD><a href="http://www.faxsav.com">http://www.faxsav.com</a>
<DT>Accessing The Internet By E-mail
<DD><a
href="ftp://rtfm.mit.edu/pub/usenet/news.answers/internet-services/access-via-email">ftp://rtfm.mit.edu/pub/usenet/news.answers/internet-services/access-via-email</a>
