<HEAD>
<TITLE> Proposed Legislation to Ensure the Legality of Employee Participation Programs and Committees</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER>
<img src="/gif/k-s2b.gif"><p>
<HR><P>
<H1>Proposed Legislation to Ensure the Legality of Employee Participation Programs and Committees</H1><P>
<HR></CENTER>
<P>
The National Labor Relations Board has issued several decisions holding that certain employee participation programs and employee committees violate the National Labor Relations Act. <P>
Because of these NLRB cases, many employers who are committed to employee participation and involvement in the workplace run the risk that continuation of these programs may violate the law.<P>
Bills have been introduced in both the House and Senate to correct this situation. Both versions of this pending legislation, called the "Teamwork for Employees and Management Act of 1995" or "TEAM," have the objective of protecting an employer’s right "to establish, assist, maintain or participate in any organization in which workers may discuss issues relating to terms and conditions of employment." The House Bill, HR743, passed the House by a vote of 221 to 202 on September 27, 1995. The Senate Bill, S.295, introduced by Sen. Kassenbaum (R. Kansas) is pending before the Senate Labor and Human Resources Committee.<P>
If you are interested in this pending legislation and its chances for passage, feel free to contact <A HREF="http:/htm/hester.htm">Ted Hester</A> in our Washington office (phone: 202/626-2901).
<P>
<center><HR><p>
<A HREF="http:/default.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/hp.gif" ALT="[Home Page]"></A> <A HREF="http:/menu/groups.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/pg.gif" ALT="[Practice Groups]"></A> <A HREF="http:/menu/attorn.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/atty.gif" alt="[Attorneys]"></A><br><A HREF="http:/menu/articles.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/art1.gif" alt="[Articles]"></A> <A HREF="http:/menu/leglink.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/lr.gif" alt="[Legal Resources]"></A> <A HREF="http:/menu/recruit.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/recruit.jpg" ALT="Recruiting"></A></center></BODY>
