<HEAD>
<TITLE> § 125 Cafeteria Plan Regulations on FMLA</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<CENTER>
<img src="/gif/k-s2b.gif"><p>
<HR><P>
<H1>§ 125 Cafeteria Plan Regulations on FMLA</H1><P>

<HR></CENTER>
<P>
The Internal Revenue Service recently proposed regulations coordinating existing guidance on § 125 cafeteria plans with the group health plan coverage requirements of the Family and Medical Leave Act of 1993 ("FMLA"). <P>
The proposed regulations generally require an employer to offer to an employee on unpaid FMLA leave one or more of the following premium payment options: 
<OL>
<LI>the employee may pre-pay the premiums due for the FMLA leave period, 
<LI>the employee may pay premiums on the same schedule as active employees and 
<LI>the employee may reimburse the employer upon return from FMLA leave. 
</OL>

Premiums may be paid on a pre-tax or after-tax basis, but special rules apply if an FMLA leave spans more than one plan coverage year.<P>
The proposed regulations also contain special rules that apply to health flexible spending accounts. Please note that this article is intended only as a brief summary of certain provisions of the new proposed regulations. If you would like further information regarding the proposed regulations, please contact a member of our group.
<P>
<center><HR><p>
<A HREF="http:/default.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/hp.gif" ALT="[Home Page]"></A> <A HREF="http:/menu/groups.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/pg.gif" ALT="[Practice Groups]"></A> <A HREF="http:/menu/attorn.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/atty.gif" alt="[Attorneys]"></A><br><A HREF="http:/menu/articles.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/art1.gif" alt="[Articles]"></A> <A HREF="http:/menu/leglink.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/lr.gif" alt="[Legal Resources]"></A> <A HREF="http:/menu/recruit.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/recruit.jpg" ALT="Recruiting"></A></BODY>
