  <li>	Counsel in a sensitive civil RICO case also needs to understand the Department of Justice's
policies and guidelines for civil and criminal RICO cases as set forth in the Department of
Justice Manual.  <i>See</i> United States Dep't of Justice, Department of Justice Manual 9-110.000 et
seq. (1990).  The Manual states that "these guidelines . . . make clear not every case in which
technically the elements of a RICO violation exist, will result in the approval of a RICO charge[and that] it is not the policy of the Criminal Division to approve 'imaginative' prosecutions
under RICO which are far afield from the congressional purpose of the RICO statute."  <i>Id</i> at
9-110.200, at 2.</li>
</ol>
</SMALL><p>

