<head>
<title>Litigation Support</title>
<meta name="CreatedBy" content="WP Internet Publisher 6.1">
</head>
<body bgcolor="ffffff" body text="#000000" body link="#00009c" body vlink="#8e2323">

<center><img src="/gif/k-s2b.gif"><p>
<h1>Litigation Support</h1>
<HR><p>
</center>
<p>
King & Spalding has long recognized the power of technology to improve its lawyers' productivity while greatly reducing clients' litigation costs.  In 1993 King & Spalding made a substantial capital investment in document imaging technology and established an in-house Litigation Support Department to better serve its clients.  King & Spalding is one of the only law firms in the Southeast that currently offers this range of litigation support services in-house.
<P>
Document imaging—producing a digital picture or "image" of a document—replaces the need to duplicate original documents in litigation, provides simultaneous access to documents by remote users, and maintains the quality of originals.  Imaging is most effective when used in conjunction with document coding—the summarization of documents into a computerized database—or OCR scanning, which enables full text searching of all documents.
<P>
A document imaging network at King & Spalding enables the lawyers and legal assistants working on a case to access the imaged documents from their desk top PC with just a few keystrokes.  Document imaging and coding saves clients significant dollars in terms of attorney and legal assistant time, copying charges, and storage and retrieval time during the life of a case.  There is no charge to clients for "computer time" or other hardware and software costs associated with use of the imaging network.
<P>
The Firm is qualified to handle both large and small document projects.  King & Spalding employs two full-time Litigation Support Managers as well as a trained staff of document coders and scanners who work exclusively on these matters.  During the past two years, the Firm has imaged or coded more than five million pages of documents.
<P>
King & Spalding Document Coders code the documents "on-line" directly into the database, cutting out the steps of completing coding forms by hand and subsequent data entry.  Quality control is performed on a daily basis for both imaging and coding.
<P>
Having in-house capability for imaging, coding and other Litigation Support services provides clients the additional benefit of safeguarding the confidentiality of sensitive documents.  All of the document coders and scanners are required to sign confidentiality agreements upon hiring.  Security is built into the imaging software; only those individuals working on a particular matter have access to those images.<P><P>
<center><HR><p>
<A HREF="http:/default.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/hp.gif" ALT="[Home Page]"></A> <A HREF="http:/menu/groups.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/pg.gif" ALT="[Practice Groups]"></A> <A HREF="http:/menu/attorn.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/atty.gif" alt="[Attorneys]"></A><br><A HREF="http:/menu/articles.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/art1.gif" alt="[Articles]"></A> <A HREF="http:/menu/leglink.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/lr.gif" alt="[Legal Resources]"></A> <A HREF="http:/menu/recruit.htm"><IMG SRC="/gif/recruit.jpg" ALT="Recruiting"></A>
</body>
