<H1><A NAME = funding></A>Funding 
and outlook for the CCSA</H1>
The CCSA was originally funded under Canada's Drug Strategy to the tune of $2 million per year, but is 
now receiving less than 40% of that original annual allocation.  The Strategy sunsets this year, and the 
Centre has been told that no further funding will be forthcoming after this fiscal year.  The crunch has 
come this year with a 50% cut in core funding (from government) over last year's allocation.  Last year, 
the Centre was able to generate 38% of its budget from revenue received from the sale of products and 
services.  Efforts towards financial self-sufficiency continue;  however, the drastic reduction in core 
funding seriously jeopardizes the future of the Centre.<P>
If you have found this Web site and the other products and services of the Centre to be useful and 
valuable, please consider making a tax-deductible donation to the Centre.  Please contact our Chief 
Executive Officer if you have questions about the funding of the Centre, and would like to offer your 
support:<P>
Jacques LeCavalier<BR>
Chief Executive Officer<BR>
Canadian Centre on Substance Abuse<BR>
75 Albert St., Suite 300<BR>
Ottawa, Ontario Canada  K1P 5E7<BR>
(613) 235-4048 ext.229<BR>
Fax: (613) 235-8101<BR>
E-mail:  jlecaval@ccsa.ca<P>
