<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Canadian Centre on Substance Abuse - Who are we</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR=#999999 TEXT=#000000 LINK=#3300ff VLINK=#660099>
<FONT COLOR=#ffffff><H1>Who we are</H1></FONT>
<IMG SRC="/ccsa2.gif" WIDTH=574 HEIGHT=20><P>
<P>
<B>The Canadian Centre on Substance Abuse (CCSA) is an arms-length, national agency, 
established in 1988 by an Act of Parliament.  Funded by Canada's Drug Strategy and 
through its own revenue-generating efforts, the Centre<P>
<UL>
<LI>promotes informed debate on substance abuse issues and encourages public participation in reducing the harm associated with drug abuse
<LI>disseminates information on the nature, extent and consequences of substance abuse
<LI>supports and assists organizations involved in substance abuse treatment, prevention and educational 
programming.
</UL>
<P>
The Centre is structured as a corporation, with a chair and a board of directors.  It 
employs a staff of 13 (full- and part-time), and has an 
<A HREF="/funding.htm">annual budget of approximately $1 million.</A></B><P>
<P>
