<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>CCSA Search</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY>
<H1>CCSA Search</H1>
Full-text searching is now available from CCSA's Web site.<P><HR>
<H3><A HREF="http:/plweb-cgi/fastweb.exe?searchform">To search the databases, click here.</A></H3>
<HR>
The following databases are available:
<H3>WWW-CCSA-CCLAT</H3>
This is a database of all HTML pages available on CCSA's Web site.<P>
<B>Sample searches:</B><P>
<UL>
<LI>fetal alcohol syndrome
<LI>workplace substance abuse
</UL><P><HR>
<H3>CANBASE</H3>
This is the Canadian bibliographic database of substance abuse related materials. CANBASE is the national bibliographic database of Canadian substance abuse publications.  It is created from contributions from the members of the Canadian Substance Abuse Information Network (CSAIN), which is a consortium of the major substance abuse libraries and resource centres in Canada.  <A HREF="/canbcont.htm">The "Contribution" field shows which network member submitted that record.</A>
<P>
<B>Approximate size:</B> 8,000 records<P>
<B>Sample searches:</B><P>
<UL>
<LI>FAS/FAE prevention
<LI>alcohol policy
</UL><P><HR>
<H3>TREATMENT</H3>
This is a database of substance abuse treatment services available in Canada.<P>
<B>Approximate size:</B> 1,200 records<P>
<B>Sample searches:</B><P>
<UL>
<LI>adolescents vancouver
<LI>methadone toronto
</UL>
<P><HR>
<H3>EAP</H3>
This is the database of Employee Assistance Programs and Services in Canada.<P>
<B>Approximate size:</B> 333 records<P>
<B>Sample searches:</B><P>
<UL>
<LI>Toronto family therapy
<LI>New Brunswick psychological testing
</UL><P><HR>
<H3>EDUCATE</H3>
The database of addiction education programs offered by Canadian post-secondary institutions.  It includes certificate, diploma and degree programs and addiction-related courses within various faculties and departments.<P>
<B>Approximate size:</B> 66 records<P>
<STRONG>Sample Searches:</STRONG>
<UL>
<LI>counselling certificate
<LI>practicum BC
</UL><HR>
