<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Guide to Employee Assistance Programs and Services in Canada </TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR=#ffffff>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="/eapguide.gif" ALT="Guide to Employee Assistance Programs and Services in Canada "><P><P><BR CLEAR=left>
<HR><P>The <B>Guide to Employee Assistance Programs and Services in Canada</B> contains detailed information on more than 200 providers of services for employees with personal and family problems, including abuse of alcohol and other drugs. This 380-page bilingual directory will tell you . . .
<UL>
<LI>the kinds of services available
<LI>whether providers are accredited
<LI>level of staff qualifications
<LI>number of current contracts held by each provider
</UL>
The Guide is published by the Canadian Centre on Substance Abuse, in cooperation with the Labour Branch of Human Resources Development Canada, and costs $20, plus GST, shipping and handling. Whether you are considering an EAP for the first time, or tendering out for your existing program, the Guide will be indispensible.<P>
<P><I><B><A HREF="/ordeap.htm">To place an order for this publication, click here.</A></B></I><P><HR>
