<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>Profile of the CCSA</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY BGCOLOR=#999999>
<FONT COLOR=#ffffff><H1>Profile of the CCSA</H1></FONT>
<IMG SRC="/ccsa2.gif" WIDTH=574 HEIGHT=20><P><P>
<FONT COLOR=#ffff00><H2>Policy, Research and Information</H2></FONT>
<STRONG>The Policy, Research and Information Unit identifies new research developments and provides technical 
support to the Centre and its key stakeholders.  Policy analysts and research associates focus on 
bridging the gap between research and policy, making research more relevant to community groups, law 
enforcement officials and policy makers.<P>
<P><FONT COLOR=#ffff00><H2>National Clearinghouse</H2></FONT>
The Clearinghouse has a full and part-time staff of six.  Staff time is divided between two major efforts:  
development of information products, and provision of information services.  One of the primary reasons 
for the creation of the Clearinghouse was to fill the gaps in substance abuse information in Canada, and to 
disseminate that information to those needing it.  The Clearinghouse coordinates the <A HREF="/csaine.htm">Canadian Substance 
Abuse Information Network (CSAIN),</A> whose members exchange information, share resources, and 
develop new information products.<P>
<P>
<FONT COLOR=#ffff00><H2>Liaison and Coordination</H2></FONT>
The goal of Liaison and Coordination is to create opportunities for dialogue and exchange among the 
Centre's various partners, nationally and internationally.  This work is focused on several key areas, 
including:<P>
<UL>
<LI>Workplace issues
<LI>Youth-related issues
<LI>Partnerships among different sectors
</UL>
<P>
<FONT COLOR=#ffff00><H2>Communications</H2></FONT>
The Communications Unit is responsible for publishing high quality print products, including the Centre's 
newsletter, <A HREF="/aneng.htm">Action News</A>.  Communications staff are also involved in a variety of non-publishing 
activities, or in projects where publishing is not the primary goal.  These endeavors include  providing background and assistance to the news media on a wide range of current issues.</STRONG><P>
<HR>
