<TITLE>Award of Distinction</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY>
<IMG ALIGN=LEFT SRC="/awards.gif" WIDTH=200 HEIGHT=238 VSPACE=10 HSPACE=10>
<BR><BR><BR><CENTER><H1>Canadian Centre<BR>on Substance Abuse<BR><BR>AWARD OF DISTINCTION</H1></CENTER><BR CLEAR=left><HR>
<UL>
<LI>Acknowledges Canadian achievement in reducing the harm associated with alcohol and other drugs
<LI>Brings peer recognition to a wide spectrum of volunteers and professionals working in drug 
prevention, education and information; treatment; enforcement; research; and policy
<LI>Focuses attention on the national stage (through the Award of Distinction) and on the 
provincial/territorial level (through the <A HREF="/seekinge.htm">Medallions of Distinction</A>)
<LI>Is presented annually, in November, during <A HREF="/daw95.htm">Drug Awareness Week</A> and National Addictions 
Awareness Week celebrations
<LI>The Award, an original bronze sculpture by a Canadian artist, depicts the individual and collective 
strength of the human spirit
</UL>
