<HTML><HEAD>
<TITLE>National Clearinghouse on Substance Abuse - Pricing policies</TITLE>
</HEAD><BODY>
<IMG SRC="/info$.gif" WIDTH=399 HEIGHT=128 ALT="Information Services"><P>
<HR>
The reference staff of the <B>National Clearinghouse on Substance Abuse</B> will respond to information requests 
on issues related to alcohol, tobacco and other drugs.  The Clearinghouse maintains an extensive document 
collection related to the nature, extent and consequences of the use of alcohol, tobacco and other drugs in 
Canada.  In addition, several databases have been developed to assist in providing information on these 
issues.  These include:<P>
<H4>CANBASE</H4>
Contains bibliographic information for substance abuse related documents and other media housed in 
libraries and resource centres of the Canadian Substance Abuse Information Network.<BR>
<I>Approximate size: 7,800 records</I><P>
<H4>CCSADOCS</H4>
Contains bibliographic description for all documents and other media housed in the National Clearinghouse 
on Substance Abuse, with the exception of periodical records.<BR>
<I>Approximate size: 5,800 records</I><P>
<H4>DIRECTRY</H4>
A listing of Canadian organizations active in the substance abuse sector, that includes address, telephone 
and fax numbers, and contact person.  The print version of this database in the Directory of Substance 
Abuse Organizations in Canada.<BR>
<I>Approximate size: 2,100 records</I><P>
<H4>TREATMNT</H4>
An inventory of treatment services in Canada, including information such as addictions treated, number of 
beds, treatment philosophy, and target clientele.  The print version of this database is Treatment: Canadian 
Directory of Substance Abuse Services.<BR>
<I>Approximate size: 1,200 records</I><P>
<H4>CANJNLS</H4>
A Canadian union list of serials in the field of substance abuse and addictions held in the libraries and 
resource centres of the Canadian Substance Abuse Information Network.<BR>
<I>Approximate size: 420 records</I><P>
<H3>The following fees apply:</H3>
Initial consultation and inquiry of less than 15 minutes is free.<P>
In-house database searches will be charged back as follows:<P>
<UL>
<LI>Canadian clients:
<UL>
<LI>1-100 records..........$15.00
<LI>101-200 records..........$25.00
<LI>200 + records..........by arrangement
</UL>
<LI>Clients outside Canada:
<UL>
<LI>1-100 records..........$30.00
<LI>101-200 records..........$50.00
<LI>200+ records..........by arrangement
</UL>
<LI>	[Note:  Number of records refers to the total number of records <BR>
	across all databases searched.]
<LI>Photocopies..........$0.25 per page
<LI>Faxes..........$5.00+$1.00 per page
<LI>Interlibrary loans:
<UL>
<LI>Within Canada..........$5.00 per loan
<LI>To the U.S...........$10.00 per loan
</UL>
</UL>
Urgent service surcharge..........$50.00<BR>
(two-day turnaround)<P>
<I>Members of the Canadian Substance Abuse Information Network are exempt from these charges 
through reciprocal arrangements among members.</I><P><I>
</I><H4>To discuss an information request, contact Margo Hawley, 
Senior Information Specialist:  mhawley@ccsa.ca.</H4>
